      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(ui): localize skill workshop switcher",
        "body": "Splits out the i18n portion of #79745.\n\nThis PR localizes the Skill Workshop mode switcher (Board / Today) into all supported locales. It does not touch the qmd/mcporter memory path.\n\n## Verification\n\nCherry-picks the i18n commit from the closed Memory/QMD PR (#79745). This PR is purely the Skill Workshop header i18n split-out; no qmd/mcporter changes.\n\n### Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed:** Skill Workshop Board/Today switcher in Control UI must render through i18n for non-English locales instead of hard-coded English, matching how `skillWorkshop.header.*` is already localized.\n- **Real environment tested:** Local `feat/stack-rebased-20260604` checkout on Linux with Node 24.15.0. The five new keys are added to `en.ts` and generated locale bundles; translators have not run for them yet, so non-English bundles fall back to English per `ui/src/i18n/lib/translate.ts:125` and `ui/AGENTS.md:7-15`.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n  ```bash\n  pnpm install\n  pnpm ui:i18n:check\n  pnpm --dir ui test skill-workshop-mode-switcher\n  pnpm --dir ui test app-render.skill-workshop\n  pnpm --dir ui test translate\n  pnpm --dir ui test app-render.assistant-avatar\n  ```\n- **Evidence after fix:**\n\n  `pnpm --dir ui test skill-workshop-mode-switcher` (key wiring invariants, baseline):\n  ```\n  Test Files  1 passed (1)\n       Tests  4 passed (4)\n  ```\n\n  `pnpm --dir ui test app-render.skill-workshop` (rendered DOM, all locales, 18 assertions):\n  ```\n  Test Files  1 passed (1)\n       Tests  18 passed (18)\n  ```\n\n  `pnpm --dir ui test translate` (regression: existing i18n test suite):\n  ```\n  Test Files  1 passed (1)\n       Tests  11 passed (11)\n  ```\n\n  `pnpm --dir ui test app-render.assistant-avatar` (regression: exporting `createState` does not break the existing 15 assertions):\n  ```\n  Test Files  1 passed (1)\n       Tests  15 passed (15)\n  ```\n\n  `pnpm ui:i18n:check` (drift gate, all 18 locales):\n  ```\n  zh-CN: clean (fallbacks=36)\n  zh-TW: clean (fallbacks=36)\n  pt-BR: clean (fallbacks=36)\n  de: clean (fallbacks=36)\n  es: clean (fallbacks=36)\n  ja-JP: clean (fallbacks=36)\n  ko: clean (fallbacks=36)\n  fr: clean (fallbacks=36)\n  ar: clean (fallbacks=36)\n  it: clean (fallbacks=36)\n  tr: clean (fallbacks=36)\n  uk: clean (fallbacks=36)\n  id: clean (fallbacks=36)\n  pl: clean (fallbacks=36)\n  th: clean (fallbacks=36)\n  vi: clean (fallbacks=36)\n  nl: clean (fallbacks=36)\n  fa: clean (fallbacks=36)\n  ```\n\n  **Rendered switcher HTML (copied live output, `de` locale):** the new\n  test `ui/src/ui/app-render.skill-workshop.test.ts` exercises the actual\n  `renderApp(state)` render path with `i18n.setLocale(\"de\")` and dumps\n  the resulting `.sw-mode-switch` element via `outerHTML`. The\n  `<!--?lit$...$-->` markers are lit-html rehydration markers; they do\n  not affect the rendered output. The strings come from the new\n  `t(\"skillWorkshop.modeSwitcher.*\")` calls, not from hard-coded\n  literals (asserted in the same test).\n\n  ```html\n  <div class=\"sw-mode-switch\" role=\"tablist\" aria-label=\"Workshop view\" data-mode=\"board\">\n          <button type=\"button\" role=\"tab\" class=\"sw-mode-switch__opt is-active\" aria-selected=\"true\" title=\"Board view\">\n            <svg viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" class=\"sw-mode-switch__icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n              <rect x=\"3\" y=\"4\" width=\"7\" height=\"16\" rx=\"1.5\"></rect>\n              <rect x=\"14\" y=\"4\" width=\"7\" height=\"9\" rx=\"1.5\"></rect>\n              <rect x=\"14\" y=\"15\" width=\"7\" height=\"5\" rx=\"1.5\"></rect>\n            </svg>\n            <span><!--?lit$...$-->Board</span>\n          </button>\n          <button type=\"button\" role=\"tab\" class=\"sw-mode-switch__opt \" aria-selected=\"false\" title=\"Today view\">\n            <svg viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" class=\"sw-mode-switch__icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n              <circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"4\"></circle>\n              <path d=\"M12 3v2M12 19v2M3 12h2M19 12h2M5.6 5.6l1.4 1.4M17 17l1.4 1.4M5.6 18.4 7 17M17 7l1.4-1.4\"></path>\n            </svg>\n            <span><!--?lit$...$-->Today</span>\n          </button>\n          <span class=\"sw-mode-switch__indicator\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n        </div>\n  ```\n\n  Key signals in the rendered HTML:\n  - `aria-label=\"Workshop view\"` — from `t(\"skillWorkshop.modeSwitcher.label\")`\n  - `title=\"Board view\"` — from `t(\"skillWorkshop.modeSwitcher.boardTitle\")`\n  - `title=\"Today view\"` — from `t(\"skillWorkshop.modeSwitcher.todayTitle\")`\n  - `<span>Board</span>` — from `t(\"skillWorkshop.modeSwitcher.board\")`\n  - `<span>Today</span>` — from `t(\"skillWorkshop.modeSwitcher.today\")`\n  - `aria-selected=\"true\"` for the active Board tab (the test sets\n    `skillWorkshopMode: \"board\"` and asserts this matches the active\n    button).\n\n  The same test runs against six non-English locales (`de`, `es`,\n  `ja-JP`, `zh-CN`, `ar`, `fr`) and asserts the same English strings\n  resolve, since the new keys are in `fallbackKeys` for every\n  non-English bundle until translators ship. Once translators run and\n  `pnpm ui:i18n:sync` regenerates the locale files, the visible\n  strings will switch to the translated equivalents automatically —\n  the test continues to assert the wiring is correct, only the\n  expected text values change.\n\n  The five strings in the diff are the same five that used to be\n  hard-coded in `renderSkillWorkshopHeaderControls`\n  (`ui/src/ui/app-render.ts:289-321`).\n- **Observed result after fix:** `t(\"skillWorkshop.modeSwitcher.label\")` returns `\"Workshop view\"`, the Board button renders with `title=\"Board view\"` and visible text `\"Board\"`, the Today button renders with `title=\"Today view\"` and visible text `\"Today\"`. Click handlers still swap `state.skillWorkshopMode` between `\"board\"` and `\"today\"`. Non-English locales resolve the new keys to English until translators run. No live Control UI build was required — the rendered HTML is the actual output of the real `renderApp` render path with the real `t()` resolution.\n- **What was not tested:** Live Control UI screenshot in a non-English locale (no Control UI build is available in this environment; the rendered HTML above is \"copied live output\" of the same render path the Control UI uses). Screen reader announcement of the new `aria-label`. RTL rendering in `ar` / `fa` for the switcher (the existing `skillWorkshop.header.*` keys do not have a known RTL regression either; defer until translators surface one). The `fallbackKeys` entries in every `<locale>.meta.json` will be replaced by real translations on the next `pnpm ui:i18n:sync` pass after translators run; that is outside this PR.\n\n### Notes for the merging maintainer\n\nThis PR is built on `feat/stack-rebased-20260604`, which carries the prerequisite `skillWorkshop` keys in `en.ts` and the `setSkillWorkshopMode` reducer. `origin/main` does not have those yet (`git show origin/main:ui/src/i18n/locales/en.ts | grep skillWorkshop` returns nothing), so this PR should land as part of the same forward-port as the rest of that stack, or the prerequisite commits should be brought in first. No conflict expected with the current `origin/main` locale bundles because the prerequisite `en.ts` and `app-render.ts` changes are the same ones this PR is wired against.\n\n## Related\n\n- Memory/QMD: isolate mcporter sidecars per agent #79745 (memory fix PR — i18n split out)\n- qmd-manager leaks XDG_CONFIG_HOME / XDG_CACHE_HOME to all child spawns, breaking mcporter ≥ 0.10 integration #79847 (underlying qmd/mcporter bug)\n",
